  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "D+21W8FI+c4eXFLPANDwZpUFgDs=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nIn `createBrowserReactor()`, the Swarm channel is wired through `ReactorBuilder.withSync(syncBuilder)` rather than `withChannelScheme(...)`. This avoids monkey-patching or SQL hacks.\n\n## Evidence\nFrom the source: \"The ReactorBuilder has two code paths: 1) `if (this.channelScheme)` \u2014 auto-creates a single factory type; 2) `else if (this.syncBuilder)` \u2014 uses YOUR factory. By using path 2, we get full control over which channel types are available.\"\n\nThe build-time registration looks like:\n\n```typescript\nconst { syncBuilder, registerGqlFactory } = createSwarmSyncBuilder(logger, jwtHandler);\nnew ReactorBuilder().withSync(syncBuilder).withJwtHandler(jwtHandler);\n```\n\n## Consequences\n- Swarm remotes persist in `sync_remotes` and are recreated natively on startup.\n- No dynamic re-registration or private-API reach-ins.\n- Rejects hacks: \"No monkey-patching. No SQL hacks. No dynamic re-registration.\"\n\n## Source\n`connect/src/utils/reactor.ts`; Swarm Channel Architecture, \"Wiring Into createBrowserReactor\".",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
    }
  },
